text: Fatehnagar is a town and a municipality in Udaipur district in the state of Rajasthan, India. ==Demographics== India census, Fatehnagar had a population of 19,624. Males constitute 51% of the population and females 49%. Fatehnagar has an average literacy rate of 60%, higher than the national average of 59.5%: male literacy is 71%, and female literacy is 48%. In Fatehnagar, 14% of the population is under 6 years of age. ==References== Category:Cities and towns in Udaipur district
